EFF deputy president Floyd Shivambu tweeted his thoughts on what happened at the May Day rally in Bloemfontein on Monday, May 1.President Jacob Zuma was scheduled to address workers at the Cosatu Workers Day rally in Bloemfontein, but he was met with boos from the workers who refused to be addressed by the president. Well done to all workers in South Africa who refused in Bloemfontein, Polokwane and Durban to be addressed by Gupta controlled thugs. Bravo! he tweeted.Well done to all workers in South Africa who refused in Bloemfontein, Polokwane and Durban to be addressed by Gupta controlled thugs. Bravo!&mdash; Floyd Shivambu (@FloydShivambu) May 1, 2017The lousy analysis of the stealing elite will be: &quot;now cosatu joined white monopoly capital, racists&amp; opposition forces&quot;. They&#39;re crumbling.&mdash; Floyd Shivambu (@FloydShivambu) May 1, 2017It&#39;s decidedly wrong for Cosatu to cancel the whole #WorkersDay rally because of 1 person. They should asked him to go and proceed. Simple.&mdash; Floyd Shivambu (@FloydShivambu) May 2, 2017 Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za